While SAA is provided with yet another massive bail-out from National Treasury (R2,2 billion), the DA-led City of Cape Town is getting its priorities right.The City is moving forward with poverty alleviation mechanisms by providing financial relief to residents who need it most.In its most pro-poor budget yet, the total cost of the social package for 2017/18 amounts to R2,7 billion, which is up from R2,5 billion last year.The proposed social package to assist in relieving some of the financial burden experienced by poor households is as follows:&nbsp;